<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2678] partition level lag metrics can be negative</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2678</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, the per partition level lag metric can be negative since the last committed offset can be smaller than the follower&apos;s offset. This is a bit confusing to end users. We probably should lower bound it by 0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
